es made through the `DataSet` are sent to the data source is important."},{"content":"For example, if a primary key value for an existing row is updated, and a new row has been added with the new primary key value as a foreign key, it is important to process the update before the insert.","pos":[9813,10015]},{"content":"You can use the <ph id=\"ph1\">`Select`</ph> method of the <ph id=\"ph2\">`DataTable`</ph> to return a <ph id=\"ph3\">`DataRow`</ph> array that only references rows with a particular <ph id=\"ph4\">`RowState`</ph>.","pos":[10022,10156],"source":"You can use the `Select` method of the `DataTable` to return a `DataRow` array that only references rows with a particular `RowState`."},{"content":"You can then pass the returned <ph id=\"ph1\">`DataRow`</ph> array to the <ph id=\"ph2\">`Update`</ph> method of the <ph id=\"ph3\">`DataAdapter`</ph> to process the modified rows.","pos":[10157,10277],"source":" You can then pass the returned `DataRow` array to the `Update` method of the `DataAdapter` to process the modified rows."},{"content":"By specifying a subset of rows to be updated, you can control the order in which inserts, updates, and deletes are processed.","pos":[10278,10403]},{"pos":[10412,10419],"content":"Example","linkify":"Example","nodes":[{"content":"Example","pos":[0,7]}]},{"content":"For example, the following code ensures that the deleted rows of the table are processed first, then the updated rows, and then the inserted rows.","pos":[10423,10569]},{"pos":[11382,11427],"content":"Use a DataAdapter to Retrieve and Update Data","linkify":"Use a DataAdapter to Retrieve and Update Data","nodes":[{"content":"Use a DataAdapter to Retrieve and Update Data","pos":[0,45]}]},{"content":"You can use a DataAdapter to retrieve and update the data.","pos":[11431,11489]},{"content":"The sample uses DataAdapter.AcceptChangesDuringFill to clone the data in the database.","pos":[11499,11585]},{"content":"If the property is set as false, AcceptChanges is not